Section 1:
1 L.D. 1738
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 1156,
9 L.D. 1738, “An Act to Establish the Biohazard Waste Disposal Grant Program to Support
10 Public Health Efforts in the State”
11 Amend the amendment by inserting after the 5th instructional paragraph the following:
12 'Amend the bill in section 2 in §1342 by inserting after subsection 2 the following:
13 '3. Matching funds from opioid settlement resources. A municipality that receives
14 opioid settlement funds and submits an application for funding under the program shall
15 contribute matching funds from its opioid settlement allocation equal to the amount
16 requested from the program. The matching funds must be dedicated to eligible uses as
17 described in subsection 7.' '
18 Amend the amendment by inserting after the 6th instructional paragraph the following:
19 'Amend the bill in section 2 in §1342 in subsection 3 in paragraph B in the last line
20 (page 1, line 25 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and"
21 Amend the bill in section 2 in §1342 in subsection 3 in paragraph C in the first line
22 (page 1, line 26 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "." and inserting the following: ';
23 and'
24 Amend the bill in section 2 in §1342 in subsection 3 by inserting after paragraph C the
25 following:
26 'D. For a municipality required to provide matching funds pursuant to subsection 4,
27 documentation of the amount and source of matching funds, including a signed
28 attestation that the matching funds are derived from opioid settlement allocations and
29 will be used in accordance with subsection 7.' '
30 Amend the amendment by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
31 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
32 allocations are made.
33 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
34 Biohazard Waste Disposal Grant Program Fund N547
35 Initiative: Provides allocations to establish a fund and authorize expenditures.
Page 1 - 132LR2340(09)
SENATE AMENDMENT
SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 1156, L.D. 1738
1 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
2 All Other $500 $500
3 __________ __________
4 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $500 $500
51 '
6 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
7 section number to read consecutively.
8 SUMMARY
99 This amendment requires a municipality that receives opioid settlement funds to
1100 contribute matching funds from its opioid settlement allocation and to provide
1111 documentation attesting to those matching funds. The amendment also removes the
1122 funding provided in Committee Amendment "A" for a position to administer the Biohazard
1133 Waste Disposal Grant Program.
1144 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
1155 (Senator ROTUNDO, M.)
1166 COUNTY: Androscoggin
